======================================================================
QUIVER REPRESENTATIONS, DYNKIN DIAGRAMS & TOURNAMENTS
======================================================================

======================================================================
PART 1: GABRIEL'S THEOREM — POSITIVE ROOT COUNTS
======================================================================

Gabriel's Theorem: # indecomposable reps = # positive roots = n(h+1)/2
where n=rank, h=Coxeter number.

  A_1: |Phi+| =    1 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 1, h= 2) OK
  A_2: |Phi+| =    3 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 4, h= 3) FAIL
  A_3: |Phi+| =    6 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 7, h= 4) FAIL
  A_4: |Phi+| =   10 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 12, h= 5) FAIL
  A_5: |Phi+| =   15 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 17, h= 6) FAIL
  A_6: |Phi+| =   21 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 24, h= 7) FAIL
  A_7: |Phi+| =   28 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 31, h= 8) FAIL  = 28 = C(8,2)
  D_4: |Phi+| =   12 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 14, h= 6) FAIL  = 12 = h(E_6)
  D_5: |Phi+| =   20 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 22, h= 8) FAIL
  D_6: |Phi+| =   30 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 33, h=10) FAIL
  E_6: |Phi+| =   30 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 39, h=12) FAIL  = 6*6 = rank^2
  E_7: |Phi+| =   42 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 66, h=18) FAIL  = 7*9 = 63 = H_forb_2 * KEY_2 = 7*3^2
  E_8: |Phi+| =   56 (expected n(h+1)/2 = 124, h=30) FAIL  = 120 = |BI| = |S_5| = |Aut(Petersen)|

