======================================================================
PART 8: GABRIEL NUMBERS AND THE PERMANENT MOAT
======================================================================

  Gabriel's theorem gives |Phi+(Q)| = n(h+1)/2 for Dynkin Q.
  These 'Gabriel numbers' for the exceptional types:
    E_6: G = 30 = 6*13//2
    E_7: G = 42 = 7*19//2
    E_8: G = 56 = 8*31//2

  GABRIEL NUMBER - MOAT CONNECTION:
    G(E_6) = 36 = C(9,2)
    G(E_7) = 63 = 7*9 = 7*3^2 = H_forb_1 * KEY_2^2
    G(E_8) = 120 = |BI| = |S_5|
    G(E_7) = 63 was FORBIDDEN at n<=7 but ACHIEVABLE at n=8!
    This is the number of POSITIVE ROOTS of E_7.
    H=63 becoming achievable at n=8 = rank(E_8) is deeply significant.

  RATIO PATTERN:
    G(E_7)/G(E_6) = 63/36 = 7/4
    G(E_8)/G(E_7) = 120/63 = 40/21 = 40/H_forb_2
    G(E_8)/G(E_6) = 120/36 = 10/3 = V(Petersen)/KEY_2

